INSERT [dbo].[voorwerp] ([voorwerpnummer], [titel], [postcode], [plaatsnaam], [GBA_CODE], [verkoper], [startprijs], [conditie], [beschrijving]) VALUES (291295242371, N'Game & Watch Wide Screen replacement polarizer, repair faded G&W polarized film', N'1072TN', N'Dalfsen', N'6030', N'vis_chros', CAST(3.5000000 AS Numeric(10, 7)), N'Nieuw', N'Does your Game & Watch wide screen suffer from a faded screen?In some of the Nintendo Game & Watch handhelds the color of the sprites on the screen has faded over time. This fading is caused by deterioration of the polarized film in the screens, making the sprites hard to distinguish and the game unplayable.Easily repair it yourself!Luckily this is easily fixed by replacing the polarizer from the screen with this new one. This sheet of polarized film is machine cut to exactly the right shape and size to fit snugly in your wide screen G&W.For step-by-step instructions on how to disassemble and reassemble your Game & Watch see this page. Before disassembling your unit make sure what the correct orientation for the new film is by looking at the screens through it. If your polarizer is oriented incorrectly the black and white of the screen will be inverted. Simply flip the polarizer over to fix this. Also make sure to remove the protective foil on both sides of the polarizers before inserting.These polarizers will fit only in the wide screen Game & Watch series. I have tested it on the game Popeye. It should fit all games with the same specifications:Parachute (PR-21)Octopus (OC-22)Popeye (PP-23)Chef (FP-24)Mickey Mouse (MC-25)Egg (EG-26)Fire (FR-27)Turtle Bridge (TL-28)Fire Attack (ID-29)Snoopy Tennis (SP-30)If you are uncertain if these replacement will fit your unit, please measure the original polarizer (link to disassembly instructions above). Measurements should be 60 x 43.5 mm. If you are looking for other sizes, please contact me though eBay.            Gemaakt door eBay Turbo Lister.   De gratis aanbiedingstool. Bied je objecten snel en gemakkelijk aan en beheer je actieve objecten.')
